\begin{figure}[H]
\centering
\begin{footnotesize}
\begin{verbatim}
                     OPTIMAL THRESHOLD COMPUTATION USING DATA VALUES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example month from dataset: 2000-Nov
    Michez difference: d_t = 0.00115539
    True recession value: R_t = 0
Candidate threshold: τ = 0.0014

1. Binary recession signal at τ:
       S_t(τ) = 1{ d_t ≥ τ }
   Using the data:
       S_t(0.0014) = 1{ 0.00115539 ≥ 0.0014 } = 0
   So the indicator does NOT signal a recession in 2000-Nov.

2. Contribution to the confusion matrix for this τ:

       If R_t = 1 and S_t = 1 → TP
       If R_t = 0 and S_t = 1 → FP
       If R_t = 1 and S_t = 0 → FN
       If R_t = 0 and S_t = 0 → TN

   Using the observed values:
       R_t = 0,  S_t(τ) = 0  ⇒  this month contributes:   TN = 1

3. Aggregating across all months t in the dataset gives:
       TP(τ), FP(τ), FN(τ), TN(τ)

   Example (illustrative structure):
       TP(0.0014) = Σ_t 1{S_t=1, R_t=1}
       FP(0.0014) = Σ_t 1{S_t=1, R_t=0}
       FN(0.0014) = Σ_t 1{S_t=0, R_t=1}
       TN(0.0014) = Σ_t 1{S_t=0, R_t=0}   ← 2000-Nov adds 1 to this count

4. Accuracy metrics at τ:

       Precision(τ) = TP(τ) / [TP(τ) + FP(τ)]
       Recall(τ)    = TP(τ) / [TP(τ) + FN(τ)]

   Using the dataset:
       Precision and Recall update when all months' contributions
       (including 2000-Nov) are summed.

5. F1 score at τ:
       F1(τ) = 2 / [ 1/Precision(τ) + 1/Recall(τ) ]

   The metric increases when the threshold τ produces a good balance
   between false alarms and missed recessions across all months.

6. Optimal threshold selection:
       τ* = argmax_τ  F1(τ)

   Meaning:
       You compute F1(τ) for every threshold candidate in the grid
       (e.g., τ = 0.0001, 0.0002, …), and the τ with the highest F1
       is reported as the optimal Michez threshold for that country.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This figure illustrates the threshold-optimization equations using actual data:
d_t = 0.00115539 and R_t = 0 for 2000-Nov.
\end{verbatim}
\end{footnotesize}
\caption{Example of How Actual Data Enter the Optimal Threshold Computation}
\end{figure}
